  "text": "By default, CFNullness soundly assumes that methods may be impure. While this catches more bugs, on the Uber code base this would lead to a large number of false warnings. CFNullness has an option to assume methods are side-effect free, but no option as of yet to assume determinism. Previous work [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] has studied automatic verification of method purity for Java; it would be interesting future work extend NullAway to verify these properties efficiently.",
